Definition: at or near or toward the stern of a ship or tail of an airplane
Example: stow the luggage aft; ships with square sails sail fairly efficiently with the wind abaft; the captain looked astern to see what the fuss was about
Synonyms: fore, abaft, astern, at, or, near, toward, the, stern, of, a, ship, tail, an, airplane, stow, luggage, ships, with, square, sails, sail, fairly, efficiently, wind, captain, looked, to, see, what, fuss, was, about
Category: adv.all
